TITLE: TSMC beats profit and revenue expectations in the fourth quarter
SUMMARY: The world's largest contract chipmaker TSMC on Thursday posted better-than-expected profit and revenue for the fourth quarter of 2023.

TITLE: Morgan Stanley revenue tops estimates, but CEO warns of geopolitical, economic risks ahead
SUMMARY: Morgan Stanley reported fourth-quarter earnings before the bell Tuesday that were lower than a year ago.

TITLE: Goldman Sachs tops revenue estimates on better-than-expected asset management results
SUMMARY: Hope is building that Goldman Sachs can turn a corner after pivoting away from CEO David Solomon's failed consumer banking efforts.

TITLE: Citigroup posts $1.8 billion fourth-quarter loss after litany of charges
SUMMARY: Citigroup CEO Jane Fraser announced plans for a sweeping corporate reorganization in September after previous efforts failed to boost the bank's share price.

TITLE: Wells Fargo posts higher fourth-quarter profit, helped by higher interest rates and cost cutting
SUMMARY: Wells Fargo shares fell Friday even after fourth-quarter profit rose from a year ago.

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase profit falls after $2.9 billion fee from regional bank rescues
SUMMARY: JPMorgan is watched closely for clues on how banks fared amid volatile interest rates and rising loan losses.

TITLE: Bank of America shares fall after company reports lower fourth-quarter profit, hit by regulatory charge
SUMMARY: Bank of America's net income fell to $3.1 billion in the fourth quarter from $7.1 billion a year ago.

TITLE: Delta more than doubles fourth-quarter profit, but trims 2024 earnings forecast
SUMMARY: Delta is the first of the major U.S. carriers to report earnings this period.

TITLE: Walgreens stock plunges after drugstore chain slashes quarterly dividend nearly in half
SUMMARY: Walgreens cut its dividend to 25 cents per share to "strengthen [its] long-term balance sheet and cash position," said CEO Tim Wentworth.

TITLE: Nike sinks 12% after it slashes sales outlook, unveils $2 billion in cost cuts
SUMMARY: Nike said the plan will cost between $400 million and $450 million in pretax restructuring charges that will largely come to fruition in the current quarter.

TITLE: FedEx shares tumble 12% after weaker demand hit revenue outlook
SUMMARY: It's the second consecutive quarter FedEx has lowered its sales guidance.

TITLE: Olive Garden owner Darden beats earnings estimates, hikes guidance as sales climb
SUMMARY: Darden Restaurants, which owns Olive Garden and Longhorn Steakhouse, raised its annual earnings-per-share guidance.

TITLE: Adobe shares slide on weaker-than-expected forecast for 2024
SUMMARY: Adobe's guidance for 2024 missed analysts' estimates for revenue and profit.

TITLE: Oracle shares slide as revenue misses estimates
SUMMARY: Demand for Oracle cloud services is growing fast, but analysts had expected more overall revenue in the most recent quarter.

TITLE: Lululemon shares fall as retailer gives tepid holiday outlook despite strong start to shopping season
SUMMARY: Lululemon struck a positive tone about the holiday shopping season on Thursday, but its fourth-quarter guidance came in light of expectations.

TITLE: Facing fines, cluttered aisles and late-night mockery, Dollar General's returning CEO tries to drive a turnaround
SUMMARY: The retailer said it will put more workers in the front of the stores, slow down store openings and step up efforts to keep merchandise in stock.

TITLE: GitLab shares soar as developer tools company posts first adjusted operating profit
SUMMARY: As more of GitLab's customers are making larger commitments, GitLab is able to expand its operating margin.

TITLE: Ulta Beauty shares pop as sales climb 6%
SUMMARY: Ulta Beauty reported a jump in sales year over year and said its chief financial officer would retire in April.

TITLE: Salesforce shares jump on better-than-expected earnings report
SUMMARY: Salesforce reported on Wednesday that revenue in the fiscal third quarter increased 11% while profit topped analysts' estimates

TITLE: Nvidia's revenue triples as AI chip boom continues
SUMMARY: Nvidia called for accelerating revenue growth in the next quarter, even as executives warn that government limits on sales to some countries will hurt results.

TITLE: Clothing rental service Nuuly reaches profitability, beating rival Rent the Runway to the benchmark
SUMMARY: Urban Outfitters' clothing rental service Nuuly has turned its first profit since its launch in 2019, rivaling the performance of competitor Rent the Runway.

TITLE: Nordstrom sales come up short, echoing broader retail industry pressures
SUMMARY: Nordstrom stressed progress it's made by clearing through inventory and reducing markdowns.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch raises outlook after quarterly sales surge 20%
SUMMARY: Abercrombie & Fitch, known for its "quiet luxury" assortment, blew past estimates again and raised its full-year guidance.

TITLE: Best Buy cuts sales forecast, as holiday shoppers hunt for deals
SUMMARY: Best Buy beat Wall Street's earnings expectations, but cut is full-year sales outlook as it prepares for cost-conscious holiday shoppers.

TITLE: Dick's Sporting Goods shares jump after retailer hikes outlook as it bounces back from theft woes
SUMMARY: Dick's Sporting Goods posted earnings and sales that beat Wall Street's estimates after its stock plummeted in the prior quarter over theft concerns.

TITLE: Lowe's cuts sales outlook as homeowners take on fewer projects; shares slide
SUMMARY: Lowe's cut its full-year sales and earnings outlook as it said homeowners were taking on fewer do-it-yourself projects.

TITLE: Chinese tech giant Baidu's shares rise 2% after revenue beat
SUMMARY: Chinese tech giant Baidu reported third-quarter revenue that beat expectations, although growth was slower than during the previous three months.

TITLE: Gap shares surge more than 30% on sales, earnings beat despite muted holiday forecast
SUMMARY: Apparel retailer Gap is improving more than expected, but the parent company of Old Navy and Banana Republic still has work to do to turn things around.

TITLE: Walmart shares slide as retailer gives a cautious outlook about consumer spending
SUMMARY: Walmart beat earnings expectations as its sales rose, but the company offered a cautious outlook for the rest of the year.

TITLE: Macy's stock pops as inventory, margin improvement help profit beat estimates
SUMMARY: Macy's earnings easily topped Wall Street's expectations.
